RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 46. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAVANNAH'S SUGAR broke sharply, quickly sped clear, extended the margin on the turn, was asked for more at the three-sixteenths starting to shorten stride, held safe. RAIN OF BLESSING chased from between runners, went three then moved out four wide coming to the quarter pole, came into upper stretch five deep, held place from a belated SK'S HEART, who stumbled at the start, chased between runners exchanging some bumps past the three-eighths, moved out four wide turning into upper stretch, ran on late. HOME TOWN FAV was urged from the start, chased inside, exchanged bumps passing the three-eighths and checked near the five-sixteenths, ran on. IVY WAY stumbled at the start, brought up the rear racing off the inside, failed to threaten. LADY AMANDA chased from outside four wide, moved in a path late on the turn, faded in the stretch. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF HOME TOWN FAV AGAINST RAIN OF BLESSING ALLEGING INTERFERENCE, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

ENTRY.COMMENT: urged brk, inside, bumps 3/8 & chk'd 5/16

ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled start, bumps past 3/8, came out 4w, belatedly

ENTRY.NAME: Rain of Blessing
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased btw, 3-4w turn, 5wd 3/16, held 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside, 4-3w turn, faded

ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled start, off inside, no threat

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUTHENIAN settled at the back, made an early move outside five wide up the backstretch to take the lead about the half, was clear at the seven-sixteenths, drifted out leaving the far turn and again near the eighth pole, held sway. FIRST TO LAST broke just a half-step slowly, moved forward outside four wide, raced up close and contending for the lead between runners coming to the half, could not match strides with the winner but held second. SIDNEY'S BID settled toward the back, advanced four to five wide on the far turn and under urging, missed place. MARCUS JUNIUS was forwardly-positioned three wide early, dropped back late up the backstretch, failed to rally. COWBOY BRADLEY moved forward to set the early tempo two deep with inside then outside pressure, was overtaken up the backstretch having dropped to the rail, came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMAGINE IT was in just a bit tight at the start, settled in the back half of the field near the inside, moved out and began to advance on the far turn coming five wide into upper stretch, put in a sustained run surging late to just get up. CALL ME A DREAMER set the pace inside foes just off the rail, drifted out a bit in the stretch, was just caught. HUNTINGTON stalked from the three path early, shifted in a bit tracking in behind racing up close heading into the far turn, moved out a bit late on that bend in range, was guided back in two wide in upper stretch, secured show honors but was no match for the top pair. MACKENZIE'S NOVVA broke outwardly, raced mostly two wide mid-pack, went evenly. SYNCOPATED was in just a bit tight at the start, raced outside the eventual winner three wide into the first turn, continued just off that one three to four wide on the far turn, ran on in the stretch. GRUNION settled at the back outside three deep early, was still well back traveling nearer the fence through the far turn, came out in upper stretch and ran on. I WANNA ROCK rated inside off the pace but close up, failed to rally. DOUBLE O OTTO pressed the pace two to three wide, weakened in the stretch. CURTEIS raced at the back and was never a threat. CASINO TRICKS was up close stalking three to four wide, retreated.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAYBE IT'S TIME set a pressured pace inside, fought on tenaciously through the lane to hold rivals at bay. HUSBAND MATERIAL tucked in three then two wide racing close but just off the leaders, tracked those while saving some ground, took closer order on the far turn in behind, had room between to bid for the lead in mid-stretch but couldn't get past, was held at bay and bumped at the wire but second best. PEJA DU stalked the leading pair, moved three then four wide on the far turn, loomed a threat at the top of the stretch, ran on evenly late while bumping the inside rival at the wire. EL DE CHIMI broke outwardly bumping a rival, was caught three deep in the early going, moved nearer the rail for the second turn saving some ground, ran on evenly. MINEOLA MIKE pressed the eventual winner, weakened in the stretch. ANDREZ CONQUIST broke a step slowly and in a bit tight, settled inside saving ground mid-division into the first turn, came out five wide at the top of the stretch, ran on. MAKOTO was hard to load, bumped at the start, settled at the rear, raced mostly near but just off the rail, improved position in the stretch. BUNKER HILL broke a step slowly, shifted in and saved ground inside racing toward the rear, kicked on mildly. BOINTHEBACK raced off the rail into the first turn about mid-pack, moved out and went three then five wide on the far turn, drifted out further in upper stretch, needed more. AIRMAN was caught four wide through both runs racing off the pace and failed to menace. DEFINE was mid-pack outside three to four wide, dropped back and faded.
